author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "Public SDK derives ContextRelevanceCandidate values from item metadata with the same signals and ordering as pm next/context; CLI consumers use the SDK primitive rather than private logic; browser-safe stable types and deterministic now/author/semantic-score options are documented; focused SDK, CLI parity, barrel, packed-consumer, and exact coverage tests pass"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Give every extension the same canonical relevance inputs as pm next and pm context
value: Eliminates contradictory rankings and subprocess workarounds across packages
impact: "Makes context ranking extensible, deterministic, and SDK-first"
outcome: "One exported derivation primitive shared by CLI, packages, and embedded hosts"
why_now: GitHub #558 demonstrates published extensions cannot reproduce built-in ranking from public APIs
parent: pm-3hps
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Public buildItemContextRelevanceCandidates is exported and shared by pm context and pm next with documented deterministic metadata signals.
expected_result: Extensions can reproduce built-in context candidate derivation from @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk without subprocesses or deep imports.
actual_result: "SDK, CLI parity, exact coverage, linked-test, and packed-consumer proofs all pass."
