comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T12:42:02.602Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-14: all-status searches for ContextRelevanceCandidate, signal builder, and GH-558 found the broad pm-3hps feature store and shipped scorer pm-h3no, but no item owns promotion of the existing CLI builder; this child records GitHub #558 without duplicating the larger index-backed store."
  "2026-07-14T12:42:11.944Z",codex-root,"GitHub provenance: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/558 documents the missing public signal builder and the pm-brief subprocess workaround. Canonical implementation lineage is pm-3hps -> pm-4k6b with shipped scorer contract pm-h3no."
  "2026-07-14T12:58:57.826Z",codex-root,"TDD progress: public SDK now owns canonical item-to-relevance signal derivation; context and next are thin consumers. Focused SDK/CLI parity tests pass, including custom status, author affinity, deadline/risk/knowledge pressure, usage affinity, malformed timestamps, and deterministic ties."
  "2026-07-14T13:07:51.733Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: exact full coverage passed 287 files / 5,687 tests at 100% statements (36,748/36,748), branches (26,382/26,382), functions (7,421/7,421), and lines (35,873/35,873). Packed @unbrained/pm-cli@2026.7.14 into /tmp, installed it into a clean npm consumer, and exercised the public buildItemContextRelevanceCandidates export successfully; npm audit reported zero vulnerabilities."
  "2026-07-14T13:19:04.684Z",codex-root,"Pre-commit acceptance review found the public options omitted caller-derived semantic_similarity despite the canonical signal and item acceptance requiring a semantic-score option. Reopened only this item to add the typed map, parity coverage, and documentation before publishing."
  "2026-07-14T13:24:27.893Z",codex-root,"Acceptance correction evidence: options now accept caller-derived semanticSimilarity and emit canonical semantic_similarity values. Focused 16-test parity, typecheck, lint, zero clones, static/docstring, package boundary, token budget, full 287-file/5,687-test exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, and a freshly repacked installed consumer asserting semantic_similarity=0.95 all pass."
  "2026-07-14T14:02:02.211Z",codex-gpt5,"Review-round evidence for PR #559 and GH-558: fixed Greptile's compact-timestamp recency finding by routing updated_at through the shared strict timestamp resolver with a fixed invalid clock, preserving deterministic rejection of relative/now values. Regression cases cover compact YYYYMMDD, ISO, malformed, and non-string runtime data; full coverage is exact 100/100/100/100."
